                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Aug. 13: The contraction in price index was higher at (-) 1.74 per cent for the week ended August 1 compared with (-) 1.58 per cent a week ago. Prices of essential commodities such as cereals, pulses and sugar, however, remained high. During the corresponding week a year ago, inflation stood at a 16-year high of 12.91 per cent.                             
	 Washington, Aug. 13: The International Monetary Fund (IMF) said it would inject $250 billion into foreign exchange reserves of member nations to boost liquidity amid the global economic crisis. Employing a rarely used tool, the IMF board of governors approved the allocation of special drawing rights equivalent to $250 billion, the multilateral institution said.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 13: SAIL chairman S.K. Roongta has won the SCOPE award for excellence and outstanding contribution to public sector management in the individual category for 2007-08. Coal India bagged the gold trophy in the institutional category.                                                                                                                           
